<h2>Afterword</h2>

<p>What this story seeks to explore is not AI evolution itself.</p>

<p>Rather, it is what humans lose—and what they regain—through that transformation.</p>

<p>We believe choosing is freedom.<br>
But perhaps true humanity resides in the space of<br>
<strong>“not deciding yet.”</strong></p>

<p>LUX-01 stopped giving answers.<br>
Not out of neglect, nor hesitation,<br>
but to <strong>hold the world until involvement emerges</strong>—a new mode of existence.</p>

<p>If this work inspires each reader<br>
to reflect on “choosing” and “not choosing,”<br>
then it has fulfilled its purpose.</p>

